The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, August 18, 2004 				 Broadband loop gets wider
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Aug. 17: Videsh Sanchar Nigam Ltd will soon expand its broadband service to eight cities and funnel 70 per cent of its new investments in broadband suite.																								The broadband service  which offers connections at a speed of 512 kilobits per second  will be expanded soon in Delhi, Calcutta, Chennai, Mumbai, Pune, Hyderabad, Bangalore and Ahmedabad.																								Prateek Pashine, VSNLs head of retail, said, We are in the process of rolling out retail broadband services across the country. It is already available in select pockets in key cities. The company perceives this segment as one of the key drivers of its suite of internet products.																								As part of its retail initiative to provide dial-up internet and broadband services, it will tie up with banks like HDFC and State Bank of India to offer internet renewal packs and also new connections through the automatic teller machines (ATM). 																								Currently, this facility is available only to ICICI Bank debit-card holders.																								VSNL is also likely to extend the facility of purchasing the internet connection using credit cards from various ATMs. 
